{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "targeted_sweep2b_pool_ideology",
    "description": "REDESIGNED: Map the effect of pool ideology parameters on cascade dynamics.\nThe original sweep (targeted_sweep2) used economic_split=0.65, but at that level v26 is 10-45% more profitable than v27 \u2014 far exceeding any max_loss_pct we tested. Ideology parameters had no effect because the gap was too large.\nThis redesign uses economic_split=0.78 (closer to the v27 win threshold of ~0.82 from targeted_sweep1). At this level, the profitability gap should be small enough (5-15%) that ideology and loss tolerance can plausibly matter.\nKey questions:\n  - At high ideology (0.8) + high loss tolerance (0.40), can pools hold v27\n    even when v26 is slightly more profitable?\n  - At low ideology (0.2) + low loss tolerance (0.10), do pools flip\n    immediately to v26?\n  - Is there a threshold combination where the outcome flips from v26 to v27?\n",
    "spec_file": "specs/targeted_sweep2b_pool_ideology.yaml",
    "n_samples": 20,
    "n_parameters": 16,
    "grid_axes": {
      "pool_ideology_strength": [
        0.2,
        0.4,
        0.6,
        0.8
      ],
      "pool_max_loss_pct": [
        0.05,
        0.15,
        0.25,
        0.35,
        0.45
      ]
    },
    "fixed_parameters": {
